<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Those mages seem to be ignoring all of the limitations of Dire Charm.<P>First of all, the enchanter has to be level 59 and spend an ungodly number of AA points to be able to try it at all.<P>The magician can make his pet anywhere he wants.  We need to find a suitable creature to charm.<P>When the magician's group moves, he can leave his pet guarding in a safe place and then summon it to him.  Summon Companion does not work on charmed pets.<P>If their pet dies, they summon a new one.  We have to wait 72 minutes for another chance to make one.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra" TARGET=_blank>Xymarra Elen-gariel</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18486" TARGET=_blank>Elven Enchanter</A> of the <A HREF="http://arbiters.econfcall.com/" TARGET=_blank>Arbiters</A> on <A HREF="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5011" TARGET=_blank>E'Ci</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra/Quest/Quest.html" TARGET=_blank>Enchanter epic quest walkthrough</A>, <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra/Strategy/EnchanterStrategy.html" TARGET=_blank>Enchanter strategy guide</A>, <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/xymarra/Spells/SpellLists.html" TARGET=_blank>Printable spell lists</A>
