<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
i read through basically that whole thread, and i'll give them that they have a valid complaint. although they do stray in many places, their overall point remains.<BR>(they, in certain cases, seem to have trouble creating an organized and all inclusive arguement, but i think in the end their argument works.)<P>The majority of them do not wish to see Dire Charm nerfed. Their issue is that mages are not a necessary or useful part of the game at higher levels. They have coth which is useful but hardly makes them a required class, second rate dd's, near worthless summons, and their pet. The pet has always been classified by Verant as overpowered, and now a more powerful pet has been given to other classes. They feel slighted. I disagree with a lot of what they use to say dire charm is overpowered, but i do understand where they're coming from. I have never played a high level mage, only to level 30 or so, so i don't understand where they're coming from exactly, but its a unanimous argument.<P>I think the main reason they need an increase now is that the end result of being a mage is you get nothing. There is no point in being a mage now, because just about every other class is better in every aspect. This climax's at 59 and 60, with druids and necros making mages worthless aside from coth, but is it really worth playing a character to 60 just to cast coth? necro's and druids now trump mages in every regard (and at very high levels, enchanters too) Yes, dire charm has slight drawbacks, but nothing to make it worse than a mage epic pet.<P>That is what they're trying to say, i believe, but that's just my impression, sound right to everyone?
