Seeing the argument from both sides (50 enchanter and 52 mage), the thread does wander and strays into whineplay territory, but the gist is that since Verant has given the magician class the label of pet masters, they should have the best possible pet. <P>The summoned pet system is what is broken, not Dire Charm. The magician epic is lvl 49, 3500 HP and maxes for 67 per hit. That is the best pet we can come up with. A Dire charmed froglok jin wizard or bok knight/shaman in Seb would be better pets than epic Jabaner and if used the way a mage would use their pet, would last probably as long and do more damage over their life span. <P>Personally, I say cool for Dire Charm, but beef up the mage epic so it has more HP and more dmg max per hit than any mob that is Dire Charmable or at least bring the two levels reasonably close together. <P>I play both so I will win one way or another, but not everyone will play both classes to 50+<P>--------------------<P>Aan_01 enchanter<BR>Aal_01 rogue<BR>------------------------<BR>"..ha ha, charade you are"
