Doens't this come up from some class like every 3 months.  I mena it was just last fall that necros were complaining about how useless they were, and then before that it was wizards, then us, then before that it was.. etc..<P>Flat out Mages will always have the best SUMMONED PETS.  The are the masters at SUMMONED PETS.  We on the other hand are the masters at CHARMED PETS.  That gives us a HUGE advantage over a summoned mage pet any day, and always will, whether the pet is dired charmed or allured, or dictated.  The difference is that WE PAY for our better pet through enhanced risk to ourselves.  Dire charm can be dispelled (thus can be broken) and the mob turn on us.<P>What would a mage give up to have a etter pet.  Maybe PP have the pet cost a sapphire to cast?  Maye refresh times, something.  I for one would in a hear beat have them change dire charm to a random duration within a given time range in order to boost the level of mobs that could be charmed (say it will wear off randomly anywhere from 45 to 72 mintues but we can charm mobs up to level 49)<BR>Now if the mage would like to beef up his pet, but not be able to summon one for 5 mins after the first one dies then maybe.  But I have seen the epic pet in action.  I have watched it kill a higher level mob faster then a sk and a rogue on another mob.  I have watched an epic pet solo level 56 mobs with ease.  I have watched an epic wielding mage solo with bascially no risk to themself gaining aa point after aa point by using there pet.<P>I seriously hope Verant does not decide to nerf dire charm.  I am afraid that if they did they then may take a close hard look at regular charm as well and seeing how powerful it is.<P>As for tweaking spells in zones, well we already know how annoying that is but yes I would rather see them disable or partially diasble a spell in a zone then just nerf the spell in general (aka charming in Kael).<P>In the end game just about EVERY class can find many many things to complain about, how they aren't needed, its not what they did for the last x nubmer of levels, they have little to do in a large scale raid.<P>I am sorry its ridiculus.  Many of us spend a vast majority of our 50+ lifes raiding of which we spent most of 1 to 50 either soloing or in groups.  The dynamics change and you can't expect to do what you did in a group of 6 with a raid of 18 to 50.  You have specific duties to fulfill (even as small as many are) and its your responsibility to see those done.  If you don't like the jobs that you have, either find a way to use what you have better or in new ways, play a different class, or STOP RAIDING.  Stop going to raids thinking that your pet is going to save the day and tank any adds etc, like it may in a group.<P>The problem doens't really lie in the mage class or any class for that matter, it lies in the large scale raid format and how the dynamics differ from the first 50 to 55 levels of play.<BR>Instead of just complaining about what other classes get they need to state what there risk would be to get their better pet.  What are they willing to LOSE for a better pet.
