hrm well I don't know about you guys, but the mage I know was easily soloing things in madiens eye, chardok etc with his epic pet.  It was also fun to watch people duel the pet becuase while they may due alot of damage to it, the non dispellable damage shield on the pet tore through the PC.  You also have to remember that mages get to use their PET as there defense.  Mages get a pet that roots (mana free and constantly), you get a pet that you can throw infront of a mob while you back away to gate.  In fact, the mage  tool is one of the best at keeping the mage alive.  Especially when you look at other classes that have to use a spell which can be resisted, fizzle, interupted etc..  Oh big bad monster coming after me  /pet attack /gate.. <BR>Now compare this to enchanter hmm big bad monster coming after me<BR>/root (resisted)<BR>Get smacked<BR>/mez (resisted) <BR>get smacked some more<BR>/tash<BR>again smacked<BR>/mez (stuck)<BR>now here I am with about 100 hps left rushing to either zone, mem gate, or run away and blur in 70 secs<P>But maybe its because a majority of the mages I have seen play are on the exceptional side of most because they do not seem to have the issues that are being complained about.  They have no problems getting groups when they want them, they have little problems soloing post 50, and they have a defined role on raids to add to the damage output of the raid as a whole through their DD's, Pet, and yes summon items.<P>Face up to it, mage pets will never be able to beat a 60 warrior because that would make the mage class too unblanaced.  Seeing what a mage can do know with what is called an underpowered pet could you imagine what they could do with a pet on the equivlent of a 55 to 60 level warrior?<P>There is a reason dictate only lasts 48 seconds...  could you imagine the furor if it was indefinite<BR>And we all know the power of a level 53 hasted charmed mob.. <P>Now give that to a mage able to summon and resummon at a moments notice...<P>It would solve none of the issues they are complaining about EXCEPT make it even easier for them to solo and get them more agro on raid type mobs (looks like we need to rez the mage again, he starts nuking and the mob just summons him away) which could lead to them having to hold back/not use their pet on raids in which they may take agro from the main tank oncce they start nuking or even better they aren't allowed to nuke anymore..<P>There are so many aspects of this game that while many classes want a variety of different things, they fail to realize the impact it may actually have on them.  A buffed up pet may only make the mages situation worse.
</FONT>
