<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
"It was also fun to watch people duel the pet becuase while they may due alot of damage to it, the non dispellable damage shield on the pet tore through the PC."<P>yup, a 50 points ds on an epic pet is awesome vs melee players that focus on fast hits rather than hard hits.  each hit does 50 both ways.  of course mobs hit for 200+ so it isn't so good vs mobs.  15 hits and the pet is gone if its tanking.  pets no longer take hits since the charmed giant vs the AoW mess.  the ds is dispellable though.<P>"You also have to remember that mages get to use their PET as there defense. Mages get a pet that roots (mana free and constantly), you get a pet that you can throw infront of a mob while you back away to gate."<P>misleading.  the epic pet you talk about does not have root.  the earth pet does.  and if you think your root is resisted think about how much the 46th level (57 spell) earth pet get resisted.  literally 90% resist rate.<P>"They have no problems getting groups when they want them, they have little problems soloing post 50, and they have a defined role on raids to add to the damage output of the raid as a whole through their DD's, Pet, and yes summon items."<P>on groups, wrong.  as an enchanter i always take a melee type over a any pet class.  same or better damage output, less risk for me.  if you have the choice of a second warrior or a mage equally skilled who would you take?<P>on raids, wrong.  on most raids there are no pets allowed due to the risk of trains from bad pathing, fear, aoe, etc.  without a pet they nuke as well as we do, poorly.  no lures.  many mages just give their mana away like necros with the rod.  even when the pet is allowed it can barely hit mobs that are red to the 60 melees.  coth is nice but not required in the zones where it still works.<P>"There is a reason dictate only lasts 48 seconds... could you imagine the furor if it was indefinite<BR>And we all know the power of a level 53 hasted charmed mob.. <BR>Now give that to a mage able to summon and resummon at a moments notice..."<P>mages aren't asking for a 53rd level pet.  they are not asking for a dc nerf.  they want an aa skill for the same cost as dc that gives them a dc-like pet.  level 46 mob, hits for 120, 6k hp.  this would be far stronger than thier epic pet and thats the problem.  if a dire charm pet is stronger than thier epic then there is a problem.<P>verant did not even know that many 46th level mobs could hit for 120 damage and asked mages for a list.<P>when verant looks into it and compares i bet they will NOT see the dc limits, only the power of the pet and it will be nerfed.  there is no way verant will make the mage pet tougher, they say it is overpowered already.
</FONT>
